commit.message:
Fix arrange() to not duplicate rows

Issue was caused by using .loc with the original df's index that had been sorted. This caused duplicated rows when indices were duplicated.

Using .iloc with the sorting dataframe's index fixes this behavior.

Fix arrange() to not duplicate rows

Issue was caused by using .loc with the original df's index that had been sorted. This caused duplicated rows when indices were duplicated.

Using .iloc with the sorting dataframe's index fixes this behavior.
